The paper presents a robotic prediction agent that uses a darkforest Go engine, a fuzzy markup language (FML) assessment engine, an FML-based decision support engine, and a robot engine for the game of Go application. The paper involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques such as fuzzy logic and decision support, which are commonly found in the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The use of a robot engine for game application suggests the paper may also belong to the cs.RO sub-category. Additionally, the paper may involve computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for analyzing the game situation. Finally, the paper may also belong to the cs.GT sub-category, which deals with game theory and its applications.
